<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>404 - Page Not Found</title>
    <style>
        body, html {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            height: 100%;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }
        .container {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100%;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 0 20px;
        }
        .error-code {
            font-size: 120px;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
        }
        .error-message {
            font-size: 24px;
            color: #666;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        .error-description {
            font-size: 18px;
            color: #888;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
        .home-button {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 16px;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
        }
        .home-button:hover {
            background-color: #45a049;
        }
        .cute-image {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 300px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        @media (min-width: 768px) {
            .error-code {
                font-size: 180px;
            }
            .error-message {
                font-size: 32px;
            }
            .error-description {
                font-size: 20px;
            }
            .cute-image {
                max-width: 400px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <img src="/placeholder.svg?height=300&width=400" alt="Cute lost puppy" class="cute-image">
        <h1 class="error-code">404</h1>
        <h2 class="error-message">Oops! Page Not Found</h2>
        <p class="error-description">It looks like you're a bit lost, just like our furry friend here. The page you're looking for might have been moved, deleted, or never existed in the first place.</p>
        <a href="/" class="home-button">Let's Go Home</a>
    </div>
</body>
</html>